    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Small shrub with multiple stiff, erect stems. The broad, heart-shaped, waxy leaves have pointed tips and are arranged alternately and neatly packed hard against the stem to form a cylindrical shoot. The small flowers emerge from between the terminal leaves to form a dense spike. Each flower has white to cream petals, becoming yellow or pink at the base and has 4 stamens in unequal pairs.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_9585",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Plants up to about 30 cm tall. Leaves about 5 mm long.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_9586",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to Southern Africa.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> Namibia to Eastern Cape.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_9587",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Common, tough, salt-tolerant species found poking up though coastal dunes, where it can occur right down almost to highwater mark. &nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_9588",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_9589",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Flowers August to March.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_9590",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>There are several other regional species in the genus, but this one can be recognised by its coastal habits and characteristic flower spike.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_9591",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        }
    ],
